{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1436,"text":"In the movie \"Interstellar,\""},{"time":3320,"text":"we get an up-close look\nat a supermassive black hole."},{"time":6671,"text":"Set against a backdrop of bright gas,"},{"time":8838,"text":"the black hole's massive\ngravitational pull"},{"time":10980,"text":"bends light into a ring."},{"time":12439,"text":"However, this isn't a real photograph,"},{"time":14572,"text":"but a computer graphic rendering --"},{"time":16382,"text":"an artistic interpretation\nof what a black hole might look like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20401,"text":"A hundred years ago,"},{"time":21591,"text":"Albert Einstein first published\nhis theory of general relativity."},{"time":25216,"text":"In the years since then,"},{"time":26679,"text":"scientists have provided\na lot of evidence in support of it."},{"time":29676,"text":"But one thing predicted\nfrom this theory, black holes,"},{"time":32784,"text":"still have not been directly observed."},{"time":35158,"text":"Although we have some idea\nas to what a black hole might look like,"},{"time":38388,"text":"we've never actually taken\na picture of one before."},{"time":41191,"text":"However, you might be surprised to know\nthat that may soon change."},{"time":45494,"text":"We may be seeing our first picture\nof a black hole in the next couple years."},{"time":49682,"text":"Getting this first picture will come down\nto an international team of scientists,"},{"time":53664,"text":"an Earth-sized telescope"},{"time":55255,"text":"and an algorithm that puts together\nthe final picture."},{"time":58111,"text":"Although I won't be able to show you\na real picture of a black hole today,"},{"time":61663,"text":"I'd like to give you a brief glimpse\ninto the effort involved"},{"time":64598,"text":"in getting that first picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67477,"text":"My name is Katie Bouman,"},{"time":68938,"text":"and I'm a PhD student at MIT."},{"time":71528,"text":"I do research in a computer science lab"},{"time":73579,"text":"that works on making computers\nsee through images and video."},{"time":76901,"text":"But although I'm not an astronomer,"},{"time":79087,"text":"today I'd like to show you"},{"time":80396,"text":"how I've been able to contribute\nto this exciting project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83323,"text":"If you go out past\nthe bright city lights tonight,"},{"time":86178,"text":"you may just be lucky enough\nto see a stunning view"},{"time":88638,"text":"of the Milky Way Galaxy."},{"time":90155,"text":"And if you could zoom past\nmillions of stars,"},{"time":92641,"text":"26,000 light-years toward the heart\nof the spiraling Milky Way,"},{"time":96420,"text":"we'd eventually reach\na cluster of stars right at the center."},{"time":99965,"text":"Peering past all the galactic dust\nwith infrared telescopes,"},{"time":103195,"text":"astronomers have watched these stars\nfor over 16 years."},{"time":107086,"text":"But it's what they don't see\nthat is the most spectacular."},{"time":110699,"text":"These stars seem to orbit\nan invisible object."},{"time":113789,"text":"By tracking the paths of these stars,"},{"time":116136,"text":"astronomers have concluded"},{"time":117454,"text":"that the only thing small and heavy\nenough to cause this motion"},{"time":120607,"text":"is a supermassive black hole --"},{"time":122599,"text":"an object so dense that it sucks up\nanything that ventures too close --"},{"time":126801,"text":"even light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128319,"text":"But what happens if we were\nto zoom in even further?"},{"time":131404,"text":"Is it possible to see something\nthat, by definition, is impossible to see?"},{"time":136719,"text":"Well, it turns out that if we were\nto zoom in at radio wavelengths,"},{"time":139987,"text":"we'd expect to see a ring of light"},{"time":141693,"text":"caused by the gravitational\nlensing of hot plasma"},{"time":144128,"text":"zipping around the black hole."},{"time":145981,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":147165,"text":"the black hole casts a shadow\non this backdrop of bright material,"},{"time":150360,"text":"carving out a sphere of darkness."},{"time":152226,"text":"This bright ring reveals\nthe black hole's event horizon,"},{"time":155589,"text":"where the gravitational pull\nbecomes so great"},{"time":158013,"text":"that not even light can escape."},{"time":159663,"text":"Einstein's equations predict\nthe size and shape of this ring,"},{"time":162546,"text":"so taking a picture of it\nwouldn't only be really cool,"},{"time":165778,"text":"it would also help to verify\nthat these equations hold"},{"time":168420,"text":"in the extreme conditions\naround the black hole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170910,"text":"However, this black hole\nis so far away from us,"},{"time":173492,"text":"that from Earth, this ring appears\nincredibly small --"},{"time":176614,"text":"the same size to us as an orange\non the surface of the moon."},{"time":180758,"text":"That makes taking a picture of it\nextremely difficult."},{"time":184645,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":186512,"text":"Well, it all comes down\nto a simple equation."},{"time":189724,"text":"Due to a phenomenon called diffraction,"},{"time":192164,"text":"there are fundamental limits"},{"time":193543,"text":"to the smallest objects\nthat we can possibly see."},{"time":196789,"text":"This governing equation says\nthat in order to see smaller and smaller,"},{"time":200485,"text":"we need to make our telescope\nbigger and bigger."},{"time":203096,"text":"But even with the most powerful\noptical telescopes here on Earth,"},{"time":206189,"text":"we can't even get close\nto the resolution necessary"},{"time":208632,"text":"to image on the surface of the moon."},{"time":210854,"text":"In fact, here I show one of the highest\nresolution images ever taken"},{"time":214495,"text":"of the moon from Earth."},{"time":215916,"text":"It contains roughly 13,000 pixels,"},{"time":218497,"text":"and yet each pixel would contain\nover 1.5 million oranges."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223396,"text":"So how big of a telescope do we need"},{"time":225392,"text":"in order to see an orange\non the surface of the moon"},{"time":228181,"text":"and, by extension, our black hole?"},{"time":230419,"text":"Well, it turns out\nthat by crunching the numbers,"},{"time":232783,"text":"you can easily calculate\nthat we would need a telescope"},{"time":235417,"text":"the size of the entire Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236834,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237882,"text":"If we could build\nthis Earth-sized telescope,"},{"time":240025,"text":"we could just start to make out\nthat distinctive ring of light"},{"time":242974,"text":"indicative of the black\nhole's event horizon."},{"time":245181,"text":"Although this picture wouldn't contain\nall the detail we see"},{"time":248123,"text":"in computer graphic renderings,"},{"time":249653,"text":"it would allow us to safely get\nour first glimpse"},{"time":251976,"text":"of the immediate environment\naround a black hole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254487,"text":"However, as you can imagine,"},{"time":256124,"text":"building a single-dish telescope\nthe size of the Earth is impossible."},{"time":259772,"text":"But in the famous words of Mick Jagger,"},{"time":261683,"text":"\"You can't always get what you want,"},{"time":263498,"text":"but if you try sometimes,\nyou just might find"},{"time":265709,"text":"you get what you need.\""},{"time":266948,"text":"And by connecting telescopes\nfrom around the world,"},{"time":269436,"text":"an international collaboration\ncalled the Event Horizon Telescope"},{"time":272998,"text":"is creating a computational telescope\nthe size of the Earth,"},{"time":276131,"text":"capable of resolving structure"},{"time":277692,"text":"on the scale of a black\nhole's event horizon."},{"time":279915,"text":"This network of telescopes is scheduled\nto take its very first picture"},{"time":283326,"text":"of a black hole next year."},{"time":285165,"text":"Each telescope in the worldwide\nnetwork works together."},{"time":288527,"text":"Linked through the precise timing\nof atomic clocks,"},{"time":291263,"text":"teams of researchers at each\nof the sites freeze light"},{"time":293944,"text":"by collecting thousands\nof terabytes of data."},{"time":296930,"text":"This data is then processed in a lab\nright here in Massachusetts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301971,"text":"So how does this even work?"},{"time":303789,"text":"Remember if we want to see the black hole\nin the center of our galaxy,"},{"time":307216,"text":"we need to build this impossibly large\nEarth-sized telescope?"},{"time":310222,"text":"For just a second,\nlet's pretend we could build"},{"time":312478,"text":"a telescope the size of the Earth."},{"time":314344,"text":"This would be a little bit\nlike turning the Earth"},{"time":316823,"text":"into a giant spinning disco ball."},{"time":318594,"text":"Each individual mirror would collect light"},{"time":320818,"text":"that we could then combine\ntogether to make a picture."},{"time":323439,"text":"However, now let's say\nwe remove most of those mirrors"},{"time":326124,"text":"so only a few remained."},{"time":328120,"text":"We could still try to combine\nthis information together,"},{"time":331021,"text":"but now there are a lot of holes."},{"time":333038,"text":"These remaining mirrors represent\nthe locations where we have telescopes."},{"time":337435,"text":"This is an incredibly small number\nof measurements to make a picture from."},{"time":341538,"text":"But although we only collect light\nat a few telescope locations,"},{"time":345400,"text":"as the Earth rotates, we get to see\nother new measurements."},{"time":348847,"text":"In other words, as the disco ball spins,\nthose mirrors change locations"},{"time":352690,"text":"and we get to observe\ndifferent parts of the image."},{"time":355613,"text":"The imaging algorithms we develop\nfill in the missing gaps of the disco ball"},{"time":359655,"text":"in order to reconstruct\nthe underlying black hole image."},{"time":362712,"text":"If we had telescopes located\neverywhere on the globe --"},{"time":365372,"text":"in other words, the entire disco ball --"},{"time":367337,"text":"this would be trivial."},{"time":368645,"text":"However, we only see a few samples,\nand for that reason,"},{"time":371991,"text":"there are an infinite number\nof possible images"},{"time":374403,"text":"that are perfectly consistent\nwith our telescope measurements."},{"time":377391,"text":"However, not all images are created equal."},{"time":380849,"text":"Some of those images look more like\nwhat we think of as images than others."},{"time":385331,"text":"And so, my role in helping to take\nthe first image of a black hole"},{"time":388577,"text":"is to design algorithms that find\nthe most reasonable image"},{"time":391533,"text":"that also fits the telescope measurements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394727,"text":"Just as a forensic sketch artist\nuses limited descriptions"},{"time":398693,"text":"to piece together a picture using\ntheir knowledge of face structure,"},{"time":402231,"text":"the imaging algorithms I develop\nuse our limited telescope data"},{"time":405570,"text":"to guide us to a picture that also\nlooks like stuff in our universe."},{"time":409916,"text":"Using these algorithms,\nwe're able to piece together pictures"},{"time":413591,"text":"from this sparse, noisy data."},{"time":415795,"text":"So here I show a sample reconstruction\ndone using simulated data,"},{"time":420348,"text":"when we pretend to point our telescopes"},{"time":422305,"text":"to the black hole\nin the center of our galaxy."},{"time":424914,"text":"Although this is just a simulation,\nreconstruction such as this give us hope"},{"time":429393,"text":"that we'll soon be able to reliably take\nthe first image of a black hole"},{"time":432870,"text":"and from it, determine\nthe size of its ring."},{"time":436118,"text":"Although I'd love to go on\nabout all the details of this algorithm,"},{"time":439341,"text":"luckily for you, I don't have the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441539,"text":"But I'd still like\nto give you a brief idea"},{"time":443564,"text":"of how we define\nwhat our universe looks like,"},{"time":445890,"text":"and how we use this to reconstruct\nand verify our results."},{"time":450380,"text":"Since there are an infinite number\nof possible images"},{"time":452900,"text":"that perfectly explain\nour telescope measurements,"},{"time":455289,"text":"we have to choose\nbetween them in some way."},{"time":457918,"text":"We do this by ranking the images"},{"time":459780,"text":"based upon how likely they are\nto be the black hole image,"},{"time":462638,"text":"and then choosing the one\nthat's most likely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465144,"text":"So what do I mean by this exactly?"},{"time":467862,"text":"Let's say we were trying to make a model"},{"time":469864,"text":"that told us how likely an image\nwere to appear on Facebook."},{"time":473071,"text":"We'd probably want the model to say"},{"time":474796,"text":"it's pretty unlikely that someone\nwould post this noise image on the left,"},{"time":478377,"text":"and pretty likely that someone\nwould post a selfie"},{"time":480820,"text":"like this one on the right."},{"time":482178,"text":"The image in the middle is blurry,"},{"time":483841,"text":"so even though it's more likely\nwe'd see it on Facebook"},{"time":486504,"text":"compared to the noise image,"},{"time":487888,"text":"it's probably less likely we'd see it\ncompared to the selfie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490872,"text":"But when it comes to images\nfrom the black hole,"},{"time":493186,"text":"we're posed with a real conundrum:\nwe've never seen a black hole before."},{"time":496712,"text":"In that case, what is a likely\nblack hole image,"},{"time":499027,"text":"and what should we assume\nabout the structure of black holes?"},{"time":501989,"text":"We could try to use images\nfrom simulations we've done,"},{"time":504645,"text":"like the image of the black hole\nfrom \"Interstellar,\""},{"time":507199,"text":"but if we did this,\nit could cause some serious problems."},{"time":510161,"text":"What would happen\nif Einstein's theories didn't hold?"},{"time":513565,"text":"We'd still want to reconstruct\nan accurate picture of what was going on."},{"time":517550,"text":"If we bake Einstein's equations\ntoo much into our algorithms,"},{"time":520945,"text":"we'll just end up seeing\nwhat we expect to see."},{"time":523724,"text":"In other words,\nwe want to leave the option open"},{"time":526024,"text":"for there being a giant elephant\nat the center of our galaxy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528971,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530052,"text":"Different types of images have\nvery distinct features."},{"time":533065,"text":"We can easily tell the difference\nbetween black hole simulation images"},{"time":536637,"text":"and images we take\nevery day here on Earth."},{"time":538937,"text":"We need a way to tell our algorithms\nwhat images look like"},{"time":542065,"text":"without imposing one type\nof image's features too much."},{"time":545865,"text":"One way we can try to get around this"},{"time":547782,"text":"is by imposing the features\nof different kinds of images"},{"time":550868,"text":"and seeing how the type of image we assume\naffects our reconstructions."},{"time":555712,"text":"If all images' types produce\na very similar-looking image,"},{"time":559227,"text":"then we can start to become more confident"},{"time":561308,"text":"that the image assumptions we're making\nare not biasing this picture that much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565505,"text":"This is a little bit like\ngiving the same description"},{"time":568519,"text":"to three different sketch artists\nfrom all around the world."},{"time":571539,"text":"If they all produce\na very similar-looking face,"},{"time":574423,"text":"then we can start to become confident"},{"time":576240,"text":"that they're not imposing their own\ncultural biases on the drawings."},{"time":579880,"text":"One way we can try to impose\ndifferent image features"},{"time":583219,"text":"is by using pieces of existing images."},{"time":586214,"text":"So we take a large collection of images,"},{"time":588398,"text":"and we break them down\ninto their little image patches."},{"time":591140,"text":"We then can treat each image patch\na little bit like pieces of a puzzle."},{"time":595449,"text":"And we use commonly seen puzzle pieces\nto piece together an image"},{"time":599751,"text":"that also fits our telescope measurements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603040,"text":"Different types of images have\nvery distinctive sets of puzzle pieces."},{"time":606807,"text":"So what happens when we take the same data"},{"time":609637,"text":"but we use different sets of puzzle pieces\nto reconstruct the image?"},{"time":613791,"text":"Let's first start with black hole\nimage simulation puzzle pieces."},{"time":618581,"text":"OK, this looks reasonable."},{"time":620196,"text":"This looks like what we expect\na black hole to look like."},{"time":622914,"text":"But did we just get it"},{"time":624131,"text":"because we just fed it little pieces\nof black hole simulation images?"},{"time":627469,"text":"Let's try another set of puzzle pieces"},{"time":629373,"text":"from astronomical, non-black hole objects."},{"time":632914,"text":"OK, we get a similar-looking image."},{"time":635064,"text":"And then how about pieces\nfrom everyday images,"},{"time":637324,"text":"like the images you take\nwith your own personal camera?"},{"time":641312,"text":"Great, we see the same image."},{"time":643451,"text":"When we get the same image\nfrom all different sets of puzzle pieces,"},{"time":646841,"text":"then we can start to become more confident"},{"time":648911,"text":"that the image assumptions we're making"},{"time":650901,"text":"aren't biasing the final\nimage we get too much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653846,"text":"Another thing we can do is take\nthe same set of puzzle pieces,"},{"time":657123,"text":"such as the ones derived\nfrom everyday images,"},{"time":659636,"text":"and use them to reconstruct\nmany different kinds of source images."},{"time":663260,"text":"So in our simulations,"},{"time":664555,"text":"we pretend a black hole looks like\nastronomical non-black hole objects,"},{"time":668354,"text":"as well as everyday images like\nthe elephant in the center of our galaxy."},{"time":672227,"text":"When the results of our algorithms\non the bottom look very similar"},{"time":675419,"text":"to the simulation's truth image on top,"},{"time":677539,"text":"then we can start to become\nmore confident in our algorithms."},{"time":680909,"text":"And I really want to emphasize here"},{"time":682800,"text":"that all of these pictures were created"},{"time":684758,"text":"by piecing together little pieces\nof everyday photographs,"},{"time":687718,"text":"like you'd take with your own\npersonal camera."},{"time":689957,"text":"So an image of a black hole\nwe've never seen before"},{"time":693257,"text":"may eventually be created by piecing\ntogether pictures we see all the time"},{"time":697224,"text":"of people, buildings,\ntrees, cats and dogs."},{"time":699993,"text":"Imaging ideas like this\nwill make it possible for us"},{"time":702662,"text":"to take our very first pictures\nof a black hole,"},{"time":705305,"text":"and hopefully, verify\nthose famous theories"},{"time":707776,"text":"on which scientists rely on a daily basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710221,"text":"But of course, getting\nimaging ideas like this working"},{"time":712853,"text":"would never have been possible\nwithout the amazing team of researchers"},{"time":716199,"text":"that I have the privilege to work with."},{"time":718110,"text":"It still amazes me"},{"time":719297,"text":"that although I began this project\nwith no background in astrophysics,"},{"time":722672,"text":"what we have achieved\nthrough this unique collaboration"},{"time":725315,"text":"could result in the very first\nimages of a black hole."},{"time":728098,"text":"But big projects like\nthe Event Horizon Telescope"},{"time":730820,"text":"are successful due to all\nthe interdisciplinary expertise"},{"time":733658,"text":"different people bring to the table."},{"time":735472,"text":"We're a melting pot of astronomers,"},{"time":737202,"text":"physicists, mathematicians and engineers."},{"time":739458,"text":"This is what will make it soon possible"},{"time":742036,"text":"to achieve something\nonce thought impossible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744913,"text":"I'd like to encourage all of you to go out"},{"time":747193,"text":"and help push the boundaries of science,"},{"time":749313,"text":"even if it may at first seem\nas mysterious to you as a black hole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753238,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754436,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}